# Canadian spelling

All user-facing copy — page titles, labels, buttons, flash messages, help text, error strings, seed defaults, and docs — must use **Canadian English** spelling.

## Common patterns

| Use (Canadian) | Avoid (US) |
|----------------|------------|
| colour, favour, honour, behaviour, neighbour | color, favor, honor, behavior, neighbor |
| centre, metre, litre | center, meter, liter |
| cancelling, travelled, modelling | canceling, traveled, modeling |
| defence, grey, cheque | defense, gray, check (payment) |
| chequing (account), paycheque | checking (account), paycheck |
| licence (noun), license (verb) | license for both |

Canadian English keeps **-ize** (not -ise): organize, categorize, recognize, analyze, realize.

## Examples

```text
✅ "Categorize this transaction."
❌ "Categorise this transaction."

✅ "Neighbourhood envelope"
❌ "Neighborhood envelope"

✅ "Cancelling import…"
❌ "Canceling import…"

✅ "Chequing" (seed account name), "paycheque" schedule placeholder
❌ "Checking", "paycheck" — US banking/income terms; Canadian banks and canada.ca use **chequing account**
```

## Scope

Apply when editing:

- **Views** — `src/views/**`
- **Flash and route messages** — `src/index.js`
- **User-visible errors** — `src/services/**`, `src/migrations.js`
- **Seed defaults** — envelope/account/group names in `src/db.js`
- **Docs and agent instructions** — `README.md`, `AGENTS.md`

Do **not** change code identifiers, URLs, CSS properties, HTML attributes, test assertions, or third-party/API terms (e.g. `color` in CSS, `ACCTID` in OFX).
